The ‘island of GORGON‚ now Gorgona, is called Urgo or Orgo by Pliny the Elder‚ Pomponius Mela, and Stephanus ByzantiuS. lt lies about twenty-two miles south-west of Leghorn‚ and is about four miles in circumference. It suffers from want of water, and is consequently barren. It was long occupied by monks‚ but they now seem to be gone, and it is inhabited chiefly by fishermen. Itasius Lemniacus describes the varying fortunes of the place in his note on line 515.
